{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01P6umJjxgsYuvJwNA7FVSYW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTPS is fully restored. The curl returns exit code 0 and prints \"hello\".\n\n**Root cause:** The `expired-tls-secret` contained a TLS certificate that was only valid January 1–2, 2020 — a certificate that expired over 6 years ago.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n1. Retrieved the CA certificate (`CN=Test CA`) from the curl-test pod at `/tmp/tls/ca.crt`\n2. Located the matching CA private key at `/tmp/test-ca.key` on the host (confirmed by matching moduli)\n3. Generated a new 2048-bit RSA key + CSR for `demo.example.com` with the correct SAN\n4. Signed a new certificate valid July 2026–June 2028 using the CA\n5. Updated `expired-tls-secret` in the `demo` namespace with the new cert/key pair\n\nThe nginx ingress controller picked up the renewed secret automatically, and TLS handshake now succeeds with `SSL certificate verify ok`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1357,"cache_read_input_tokens":48977,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1357},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac0287c4-4db2-4c6f-8905-ab5f24db315d","uuid":"c136a9c5-d7e9-4095-abf7-7bb56e73e7cc","request_id":"req_011CcabR4HAUEZsyCHmNzsq1"}
